**What they want from this post:**
A clear, honest breakdown of every service cost in one place — no guessing, no "it depends" without a follow-up number, no editorial fluff. They want to know what they'll pay before they sit down. They also want to know if they're being charged fairly.

**What frustrates them in current content:**
- Generic "prices vary" answers with no numbers
- Content clearly written for nail techs pricing their services, not consumers
- Prices that are obviously outdated (2019-2022 data presented as current)
- No international coverage — UK readers can't use US-only guides
- Missing the ongoing cost (fills, maintenance) — only first visit covered

